How much time did I use?

855
00:44:57,520 --> 00:44:59,150
Less than fifteen minutes.

856
00:44:59,150 --> 00:45:01,390
Much faster than last time.

857
00:45:04,670 --> 00:45:07,630
The formation of your school
is wonderful.

858
00:45:07,630 --> 00:45:10,080
The more I think about it,
the more interesting I feel.

859
00:45:11,470 --> 00:45:12,840
It took me a long time

860
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:14,180
to understand it.

861
00:45:15,670 --> 00:45:17,610
You’re a clever man.

862
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:19,280
You’ve learnt all our formations

863
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:21,520
when you learn for the first time.

864
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:25,200
It proves I have a good taste.

865
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,530
You’re a young talent
from the Fortress of the Forty-Eight.

866
00:45:28,950 --> 00:45:32,320
I can’t take you as my disciple.

867
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:35,950
But I want our formations

868
00:45:35,950 --> 00:45:38,700
and martial art books to be inherited

869
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:43,620
instead of vanishing with me.

870
00:45:44,630 --> 00:45:46,120
What have I done

871
00:45:46,120 --> 00:45:48,150
to deserve your gracious kindness?

872
00:45:55,010 --> 00:45:58,520
♪Stars flow like river♪

873
00:45:59,580 --> 00:46:03,180
♪My yearning falls into the river♪

874
00:46:03,750 --> 00:46:07,820
♪Now that you’re in my life♪

875
00:46:08,070 --> 00:46:11,710
♪I will never be alone♪

876
00:46:11,710 --> 00:46:15,830
♪I haven’t seen the mountains with you♪

877
00:46:16,250 --> 00:46:20,680
♪Nor have I tied up your hair♪

878
00:46:21,340 --> 00:46:25,900
♪We haven’t finished our story in chaos♪

879
00:46:26,130 --> 00:46:30,760
♪The blade hasn’t been returned♪

880
00:46:30,950 --> 00:46:34,780
♪I fear not to roam the world with you♪

881
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:39,690
♪When I go across the world for you♪

882
00:46:39,950 --> 00:46:43,690
♪I’m willing to shed blood for you♪

883
00:46:44,020 --> 00:46:49,110
♪Don’t mind whose land it is♪

884
00:46:49,110 --> 00:46:53,050
♪Where is home to the snowflake♪

885
00:46:53,050 --> 00:46:57,580
♪Come and melt in my embrace♪

886
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:05,300
♪The spring sun is an invisible armor
that’ll hold♪

887
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:10,670
♪The purest love is unadorned♪
